article.description: — Kevion Nolan had 23 points as Jacksonville beat Southern Miss 62-51 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Nolan leads Jacksonville past Southern Miss 62-51
article.linkText: Nolan leads Jacksonville past Southern Miss 62-51
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. -- — Kevion Nolan had 23 points as Jacksonville beat Southern Miss 62-51 on Tuesday night. Jordan Davis had 14 points for Jacksonville (6-3). Southern Miss scored 19 points in the first half, a season low for the team. Jaron Pierre Jr. had 18 points for the Golden Eagles (4-6), who have now lost four consecutive games. Isaih Moore added 10 points. Tyler Stevenson had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
